 ">full entry</a></span></span></span></div><div class="collapse" htag="div" hclass="collapse"><span class="unbox" id="alimony_unbox_1" unbox="wordorigin"><span class="box_title">Word Origin</span><span class="body"><span class="p">early 17th cent. (in the sense ‘nourishment, means of subsistence’): from Latin <span class="ei">alimonia</span> ‘nutriment’, meaning nourishment, from <span class="ei">alere</span> ‘nourish’.</span></span></span></div>    <div id="ring-links-box">
